1. World Tour

On the first line, you will be given a string containing all of your stops.
Until you recieve the command "Stop" you will be given some commands to manipulate the string.
Add Stop *index* *string* - insert the given string at that index only if the index is valid
Remove Stop *index *index* - remove the elements of the string from the starting index to the end index if both are indices are valid
Switch *oldString* *newString* - if the old string is in the initial string, replace it with the new one.


2. Destination Mapper

You will be given a string representing some places on the map. You have to filter the valid ones.
Valid one - surrounded by "=" or "/" on both sides. First letter is upper, others can be upper or lower. The letters must be atleast 3.
After matching all the locations. You calculate travel points by summing the lengths of the valid destinations.


3. Plant Discovery

On the first line, you will recieve a number n.
On the next n lines we recieve plant and rarity. We need to store that info. If we recieve the same plant, we update the rarity.
After that you will be given different commands until "Exhibition"
Rate *plant* *rating* - add the given rating to the plant (store the ratings)
Update *plant* *newrarity* - update the rarity of the plant with new one
Reset *plant* - remove all the ratings of the given plant.
